post_text: Wow! Time really flies when you are having fun. June 30th will be our last day of the Summer Lunch Rocks service. I would like to tell you the students, parents and the community THANK YOU for all the support. Susan Anthony, Lori Munsell, Michelle Ewalt, and all of the kitchen staff want you to know that we are so happy that we have been able to serve you every day. Susan and Lori have been so excited to see all of you on a daily basis, Michelle and Harley have looked forward to serving nutritious meals to all students at weightlifting. We have truly enjoyed serving all the students and community since March. Thank you for all of the support. We look forward to seeing you all in August!!!

Sophomores - Tuesday, May 19 from 1:00-4:00pm
Freshmen - Wednesday, May 20 from 8:30-11:30am

This meeting will cover Capital Outlay requests and Summer work, recommendations to approve USD 214's Continuous Learning Plan.

post_text:
Coronavirus Update
The USD 214 school district is closely monitoring the Coronavirus (COVID-19) situation in the United
States. This is a fluid situation with changes occurring all the time. We are receiving regular updates
from Kansas State Department of Education (KSDE), Kansas Department of Health and Environment
(KDHE) and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).

Click here for more information: http://www.kdheks.gov/ and https://www.cdc.gov/

Any new information will be posted at www.usd214.org, Facebook and Twitter.

Thank you for your continued support in this ever changing environment.

post_text:
We are in unprecedented times in dealing with the Covid 19 virus The district is relying on local, state, and federal health officials to help make many critical decisions that affect our students, staff, and our communities.

Based on a webinar today we have cancelled Spring sports practices this week.

We will continue to meet with the health and educational leaders and hope to have more information of "what's next" available by midweek.

Thank you for your patience and understanding in this difficult time.
